    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the tofu is cooking, combine the <strong>remaining grated garlic</strong> with the <strong>warmed</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>butter alternative</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>in a small bowl<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>garlic butter</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>ciabattas</strong> in half, then spread the <strong>garlic butter </strong>over the <strong>ciabatta halves </strong>(reserve the bowl)</p><p>Once the tofu is almost done, add the <strong>garlic ciabattas</strong> to a separate <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 5-7 min or until crusty – this is your<strong> Texas-style toast</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
